---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Local Heritage - Hampstead Architects"
  description="Conservation Area experts. Specialists in Grade II listed buildings, Camden Planning, English Heritage, and Hampstead Garden Suburb Trust requirements. Basement excavation with structural integrity protection."
  schemaType="AboutPage"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-padding min-h-[60vh] flex items-center">
    <div class="grid-editorial w-full">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-10">
        <h1 class="text-balance mb-8">
          Guardians of Hampstead's Architectural Heritage
        </h1>
        <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed text-charcoal/80 max-w-3xl">
          Navigating Conservation Areas, English Heritage, and Camden Planning requires more than technical knowledge—it requires deep local understanding.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Conservation Experts Section -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-warm-stone">
    <div class="grid-editorial">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-5">
        <h2 class="text-balance mb-8">
          The Conservation Experts
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-6 lg:col-start-7">
        <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Hampstead is not just another postcode. It's a tapestry of architectural history—from 18th-century townhouses on Flask Walk to Arts and Crafts gems in the Garden Suburb.
          </p>

          <p>
            Our architects are intimately familiar with:
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-4 mt-8" role="list">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-oxidized-copper flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4" />
              </svg>
              <div>
                <strong class="block text-charcoal mb-1">English Heritage Requirements</strong>
                <span class="text-charcoal/70">Grade I, Grade II*, and Grade II listed building consents</span>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-oxidized-copper flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
              </svg>
              <div>
                <strong class="block text-charcoal mb-1">Camden Planning Department</strong>
                <span class="text-charcoal/70">Pre-application advice, Conservation Area consents, Article 4 directions</span>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-oxidized-copper flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 12l2-2m0 0l7-7 7 7M5 10v10a1 1 0 001 1h3m10-11l2 2m-2-2v10a1 1 0 01-1 1h-3m-6 0a1 1 0 001-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v4a1 1 0 001 1m-6 0h6" />
              </svg>
              <div>
                <strong class="block text-charcoal mb-1">Hampstead Garden Suburb Trust</strong>
                <span class="text-charcoal/70">Design guidelines for the UNESCO-nominated suburb</span>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-oxidized-copper flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z" />
              </svg>
              <div>
                <strong class="block text-charcoal mb-1">Local Design Guidelines</strong>
                <span class="text-charcoal/70">Material palettes, rooflines, fenestration patterns specific to NW3</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Basement Engineering Section -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="grid-editorial items-center">
      <!-- Image -->
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-6 order-2 lg:order-1 mt-12 lg:mt-0">
        <div class="img-framed">
          <img
            src="/images/basement-engineering.jpg"
            alt="Technical diagram of basement excavation structural engineering"
            class="w-full h-auto"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-5 lg:col-start-8 order-1 lg:order-2">
        <h2 class="text-balance mb-8">
          Basement Engineering
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Basement excavations in Hampstead are not just about adding square footage—they're complex structural interventions in Victorian and Edwardian foundations.
          </p>

          <p>
            Our approach prioritizes:
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-3 mt-6" role="list">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-oxidized-copper mt-1">•</span>
              <span class="text-charcoal/70"><strong class="text-charcoal">Structural integrity:</strong> Temporary works design, underpinning strategies, and foundation monitoring</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-oxidized-copper mt-1">•</span>
              <span class="text-charcoal/70"><strong class="text-charcoal">Party Wall Act compliance:</strong> Proactive neighbour liaison and dispute avoidance</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-oxidized-copper mt-1">•</span>
              <span class="text-charcoal/70"><strong class="text-charcoal">Drainage and waterproofing:</strong> Tanking systems that last decades, not years</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-oxidized-copper mt-1">•</span>
              <span class="text-charcoal/70"><strong class="text-charcoal">Light wells and egress:</strong> Building Regulations compliance for habitable basements</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p class="pt-6">
            Because we're part of Hampstead Renovations, we've delivered over 40 basement projects in NW3. We know what works—and what Camden will approve.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local Case Study Highlights -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-warm-stone">
    <div class="grid-editorial">
      <div class="col-span-12 mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-balance">Recent Local Projects</h2>
      </div>

      <article class="col-span-12 md:col-span-6">
        <div class="img-framed mb-6 aspect-[4/3]">
          <img
            src="/images/frognal-restoration.jpg"
            alt="Grade II listed restoration in Frognal"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl mb-3">The Frognal Restoration</h3>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed mb-2">
          Grade II listed Georgian townhouse. English Heritage consent for sash window repairs and lime render restoration.
        </p>
        <span class="text-sm text-oxidized-copper">Conservation Area: Hampstead</span>
      </article>

      <article class="col-span-12 md:col-span-6 mt-12 md:mt-0">
        <div class="img-framed mb-6 aspect-[4/3]">
          <img
            src="/images/garden-suburb.jpg"
            alt="Arts and Crafts extension in Hampstead Garden Suburb"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl mb-3">The Garden Suburb Extension</h3>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed mb-2">
          Arts and Crafts property. Single-storey rear extension using handmade bricks and natural slate to match the 1910 original.
        </p>
        <span class="text-sm text-oxidized-copper">Conservation Area: Hampstead Garden Suburb</span>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats / Credentials -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 text-center">
      <div>
        <p class="font-serif text-5xl text-oxidized-copper mb-2">40+</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Basement Projects</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-serif text-5xl text-oxidized-copper mb-2">100%</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Planning Success</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-serif text-5xl text-oxidized-copper mb-2">15yrs</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Local Experience</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-serif text-5xl text-oxidized-copper mb-2">NW3</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Specialists</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-padding text-center bg-oxidized-copper text-off-white">
    <h2 class="text-balance mb-8">
      Let's discuss your heritage project
    </h2>
    <a href="/contact" class="inline-block px-8 py-3 border border-off-white text-off-white hover:bg-off-white hover:text-oxidized-copper transition-colors">
      Book Your Consultation
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
